\,x\in\Bbb R\;,\;\;|x|<1\,
\frac1{1-x}=\sum_{n=0}^\infty x^n\stackrel{\text{differentiation}}\implies\frac1{(1-x)^2}=\sum_{n=1}^\infty nx^{n-1}
